00:54.055 --> 00:56.349
<i>Preorder the next
Death Race now</i>

00:56.432 --> 00:58.601
<i>and you'll not only
get 20% off,</i>

00:58.810 --> 01:02.355
<i>but you'll also receive limited
edition Frankenstein merchandise.</i>

01:02.939 --> 01:05.441
<i>Frankenstein, the four-time
Death Race champion,</i>

01:05.525 --> 01:07.694
<i>has taken the world by storm.</i>

01:07.777 --> 01:09.362
<i>The most unlikely of heroes</i>

01:09.445 --> 01:10.780
<i>who has come out of nowhere</i>

01:10.863 --> 01:13.741
<i>and is now just one
win away from freedom.</i>

01:15.034 --> 01:16.160
<i>Death Race.</i>

01:18.580 --> 01:20.999
<i>Now streaming live.</i>

01:21.416 --> 01:23.496
<i>Death Race is the trademark
of Weyland International.</i>

01:23.501 --> 01:24.919
<i>Your safety's our top priority.</i>

01:29.632 --> 01:32.927
FEMALE REPORTER: <i> The notorious Death
Racer known only as Frankenstein</i>

01:33.011 --> 01:35.054
<i>won his fourth race today.</i>

01:35.138 --> 01:38.766
<i>One more victory and the masked
killer gains his freedom.</i>

01:40.685 --> 01:42.770
Frankenstein fears nothing.

01:43.062 --> 01:46.024
Anything in his way,
he destroys.

01:47.191 --> 01:51.321
<i>Under my watch, Terminal Island
and Death Race have thrived.</i>

01:51.779 --> 01:54.532
REPORTER: <i> Rumors have been going
around that Weyland International,</i>

01:54.616 --> 01:57.035
<i>the organization
behind Death Race,</i>

01:57.118 --> 01:59.871
<i>has been targeted
for hostile takeover.</i>

01:59.954 --> 02:02.373
As a businessman,
takeover talk is common.

02:02.665 --> 02:05.835
You have something of value, naturally,
people want to take it away.

02:05.918 --> 02:07.920
REPORTER: <i>British
billionaire, Niles York,</i>

02:08.003 --> 02:10.965
<i>has placed himself in the
center of a firestorm.</i>

02:11.049 --> 02:13.259
Well, I've got nothing to say
about that at the moment.

02:13.343 --> 02:15.511
But I will say this.

02:16.054 --> 02:20.391
When I want something, no one
can stop me from taking it.

02:21.726 --> 02:24.646
I'm not too concerned. I've won
more battles than I've lost.

02:25.897 --> 02:27.607
I feel bad for Weyland,
I really do.

02:27.690 --> 02:30.109
But Father Time, he's
caught up with the old man.

02:30.193 --> 02:31.861
He never really stood a chance.

02:42.789 --> 02:44.123
Good morning,
Mr. Weyland.

02:47.919 --> 02:49.587
(NILES SIGHS)

02:50.421 --> 02:52.131
Wasn't so bad, was it?

02:57.929 --> 02:59.347
I built this business.

03:00.223 --> 03:01.432
I didn't have to steal it.

03:01.933 --> 03:04.519
What you left vulnerable,
I seized. I stole nothing.

03:04.602 --> 03:08.231
You lacked vision, Weyland.
That was your undoing.

03:15.113 --> 03:16.155
Vision.

03:16.280 --> 03:17.740
(DOOR SHUTS)

03:18.366 --> 03:22.704
Is that why you're investing millions in
dilapidated prisons all around the globe?

03:22.829 --> 03:23.871
Vision?

03:25.289 --> 03:28.543
You're so far over your head, you might
as well be six feet under the ground.

03:28.626 --> 03:32.046
The prison business is not what
made this company profitable.

03:32.588 --> 03:34.590
So the conclusion to draw,

03:37.844 --> 03:39.846
you're trying to
franchise <i>Death Race.</i>

03:42.807 --> 03:45.143
(CHUCKLES)
It's not going to work.

03:45.351 --> 03:47.061
Because you couldn't
make it work.

03:47.812 --> 03:50.815
Let me show you what true
vision really looks like.

04:00.241 --> 04:02.827
You started something
beautiful, Weyland.

04:02.910 --> 04:04.912
But you only scratched
at the surface.

04:04.996 --> 04:07.707
<i>And you're right. I'm
taking Death Race global.</i>

04:07.832 --> 04:10.960
<i>By this time next year, there will
be a different race every two weeks</i>

04:11.043 --> 04:15.214
at a different exotic hellhole with
different drivers, tracks and challenges.

04:15.339 --> 04:21.053
I will have a monopoly on the most profitable
sport in the history of the planet.

04:21.721 --> 04:23.639
More cars.
More cons. More guns.

04:24.682 --> 04:27.351
More death.
The sky's the limit.

04:32.523 --> 04:33.733
(SIGHS)

04:34.400 --> 04:36.360
Well, you forgot one thing.

04:38.446 --> 04:39.739
Frankenstein.

04:40.698 --> 04:43.743
It's a man in a mask.

04:43.868 --> 04:45.995
I could have 20 Frankensteins
around the globe.

04:46.078 --> 04:47.955
How would the fans know
which one was real?

04:48.206 --> 04:50.583
Frankenstein won
his fourth race today.

04:50.750 --> 04:53.085
One more win, he goes free.

04:53.920 --> 04:55.755
That's a fact
that every fan knows.

04:56.631 --> 04:59.425
Now, if you suddenly change
the rules of the game,

05:00.092 --> 05:01.719
you're going to
lose your audience.

05:02.428 --> 05:04.972
And if you're hoping
that Frankenstein loses,

05:05.056 --> 05:07.600
well, son, I guess
there's a first time.

05:08.059 --> 05:11.479
Now, how would your
little copycat event play

05:11.562 --> 05:13.564
without the game's
marquee star?

05:14.065 --> 05:16.275
That's why you're
going to fail.

05:19.278 --> 05:21.531
What kind of cigars
you smoke, Weyland?

05:22.365 --> 05:26.160
I'll be sure to send you a box when
<i>Death Race</i> becomes a global success.

05:26.244 --> 05:30.665
It'll be the second time I've beaten you.
The second time you've lost.

05:31.916 --> 05:35.503
Well, you enjoy your
moment while you can.

05:37.255 --> 05:39.090
Payback's a bitch, son.

05:49.141 --> 05:50.476
NILES: Weyland's right.

05:50.601 --> 05:52.442
Find out who the man
behind the mask really is.

05:52.520 --> 05:54.647
What he loves, what he hates,
what he covets most.

05:54.772 --> 05:56.023
And find out what Weyland
was planning next.

05:56.107 --> 05:57.191
What do you mean?

05:57.275 --> 05:59.151
The company's banking nearly
eight million quid a week

05:59.235 --> 06:00.862
hawking Frankenstein
merchandise.

06:00.945 --> 06:02.185
He wasn't just gonna let it go.

06:02.280 --> 06:03.322
Anything else?

06:03.739 --> 06:07.159
Yeah. Get yourself some decent clothes.
You look like a bag lady.

06:07.952 --> 06:12.874
I wouldn't be here, I wouldn't have clone all
this unless I absolutely loved Death Race.

06:12.957 --> 06:16.168
So I'm speaking to the millions
of fans around the globe.

06:16.377 --> 06:18.296
Fear not.
I am like you.

06:18.379 --> 06:21.883
I seek not to destroy nor to compromise
what we've all come to revere.

06:21.966 --> 06:24.969
The <i>Death Race</i> that we all
know and love will not change.

06:25.052 --> 06:29.557
It will grow bigger and better.
This, I promise.

06:29.640 --> 06:30.683
Thank you.

06:30.766 --> 06:32.643
(INDISTINCT CLAMORING)

06:37.189 --> 06:39.984
DR. KLEIN: Overall, I have
to say I'm very happy.

06:40.902 --> 06:42.028
You wanna take a look?

06:42.111 --> 06:43.154
No.

06:43.404 --> 06:45.740
We'll run a few more
tests tomorrow,

06:46.532 --> 06:48.252
and you're back to your
old self in no time.

06:48.492 --> 06:49.493
WEYLAND: No, he won't.

06:51.162 --> 06:52.413
He'll be better.

06:54.498 --> 06:55.833
Everybody out.

06:56.834 --> 07:00.004
You heard the man.
Take a coffee break, guys.

07:04.008 --> 07:05.885
So, I guess
the rumors are true.

07:05.968 --> 07:07.428
(DOOR SHUTS)

07:07.511 --> 07:08.512
(CHUCKLES)

07:08.596 --> 07:11.182
Yeah, and I guess you won't
be shedding any tears for me.

07:12.224 --> 07:16.103
Hey, you and I, Carl, we've taken
very different paths in life.

07:17.605 --> 07:19.190
But we both ended up here.

07:19.440 --> 07:20.524
No, I'm here.

07:20.775 --> 07:24.403
You come and go as you please,
see the ones you love.

07:25.363 --> 07:26.364
They see you.

07:27.073 --> 07:29.867
Don't compare us, Weyland.
You lost the company.

07:31.577 --> 07:33.621
I lost my life.
Mmm-hmm.

07:33.704 --> 07:37.375
Yeah, and I also fixed your
face and I gave you a way out.

07:37.541 --> 07:40.169
Look at me and tell me you
were gonna keep your word.

07:41.921 --> 07:43.422
I'm not stupid, Weyland.

07:43.798 --> 07:46.717
And you didn't fix my face out of the
kindness of your heart, did you?

07:47.259 --> 07:49.637
It was infected.
I was gonna die.

07:49.720 --> 07:51.514
And you would have
lost your star driver.

07:53.391 --> 07:57.144
Yeah, you're not so bad.
You're worse.

07:58.437 --> 08:00.064
And you want me to trust you?

08:01.107 --> 08:02.900
You deserve the
shit-storm you're in.

08:03.067 --> 08:04.402
(CHUCKLES)

08:04.902 --> 08:06.904
Well, I got news for you, Carl.

08:08.280 --> 08:10.408
You're already
in waist-deep.

08:11.117 --> 08:12.702
You're Frankenstein.

08:13.703 --> 08:17.623
This all starts
and ends with you.

08:23.713 --> 08:25.339
WEYLAND: Carl Lucas.

08:26.257 --> 08:28.092
<i>Born a gangster,</i>

08:28.801 --> 08:30.261
<i>became a prisoner,</i>

08:31.387 --> 08:34.765
<i>and now, a monster.</i>

08:36.225 --> 08:37.601
(INAUDIBLE)

08:44.275 --> 08:45.693
(SCREAMING)

08:49.155 --> 08:50.823
(KATRINA WAILING)

09:03.961 --> 09:05.588
<i>May he rest in peace.</i>

09:09.133 --> 09:12.803
<i>You and your team
win five races</i>

09:13.220 --> 09:14.805
<i>and you go free.</i>

09:14.889 --> 09:18.142
<i>Goldberg, Lists</i>

09:18.601 --> 09:22.229
<i>and that beautiful,
beautiful Katrina.</i>

09:24.148 --> 09:25.816
(KATRINA GIGGLING)

09:33.783 --> 09:35.743
<i>Now, for this to work,</i>

09:37.078 --> 09:39.497
<i>you can't tell your
true identity to anyone.</i>

09:40.664 --> 09:42.708
<i>Carl Lucas stays dead.</i>

09:42.792 --> 09:44.168
<i>You're Frankenstein.</i>

09:45.086 --> 09:46.754
GOLDBERG: Well,
you're welcome, asshole.

09:46.837 --> 09:48.255
Four wins and not
even a thank you.

09:50.508 --> 09:54.553
WEYLAND: <i> This all starts
and ends with you.</i>

10:03.229 --> 10:04.855
(NILES LAUGHING)

10:06.107 --> 10:08.692
There he is.
There's the guy.

10:12.363 --> 10:14.323
I'm having you transferred.

10:14.448 --> 10:17.618
You're headed to the Kalahari Desert
Maximum Security Penitentiary

10:17.701 --> 10:21.539
in South Africa where you will compete
in the first ever <i>Desert Death Race.</i>

10:22.081 --> 10:24.708
Wow. What do I get,
my own dune buggy?

10:25.709 --> 10:28.003
Youâ€™re just on loan
to the Kalahari

10:28.129 --> 10:31.215
to help launch the first of what will
be many international Death Races.

10:31.340 --> 10:33.717
We're sending 14K,
as well as both your teams.

10:33.884 --> 10:36.137
So I'm guessing I should
get my passport updated.

10:36.220 --> 10:38.556
I get the feeling that you
are not taking me seriously.

10:38.639 --> 10:39.849
That's because I'm not.

10:40.558 --> 10:42.726
Listen to me. I made
a deal with Weyland.

10:43.477 --> 10:46.355
I win one more race,
me, my team,

10:46.647 --> 10:47.648
we're out.

10:48.315 --> 10:50.985
Yeah, well, you know,
it's a pity about Weyland,

10:51.068 --> 10:53.237
because all deals
with him are null and void.

10:53.320 --> 10:56.157
You work for me now.
New rules.

10:56.240 --> 10:57.241
No.

10:58.075 --> 10:59.577
No, I don't think so.

11:00.161 --> 11:02.601
You don't have a choice, mate.
But if you don't want to drive,

11:03.706 --> 11:04.748
fine.

11:04.832 --> 11:06.333
(GUNS COCKING)

11:08.502 --> 11:12.715
I will paint my plane
red with your blood.

11:13.048 --> 11:14.383
Really?

11:14.758 --> 11:16.093
Niles?

11:16.594 --> 11:18.095
What are you gonna do,
replace me?

11:19.221 --> 11:20.264
With Who?

11:20.681 --> 11:23.100
Why would you care?
You're already dead.

11:25.519 --> 11:30.608
So, as long as you're alive, you'll be
treated like the star that you are.

11:31.066 --> 11:32.109
Or,

11:32.568 --> 11:34.195
I could just simply
fuck up your little plan,

11:34.278 --> 11:36.280
couldn't I,
by winning one more race

11:36.780 --> 11:37.865
and I'm free.

11:37.948 --> 11:39.200
(LAUGHS)

11:39.283 --> 11:41.785
Wow. You'll never make it
to the finish line, mate.

11:41.911 --> 11:43.037
Trust me on that.

11:43.120 --> 11:47.249
You lose, you live.
You win, you die.

12:57.152 --> 12:58.362
(MEN CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY)

13:10.332 --> 13:11.834
GUARD: Okay, get out!

13:12.376 --> 13:13.711
Let's go, move!

13:14.253 --> 13:15.587
MAN: Bring that
jackhammer here.

13:16.297 --> 13:18.549
GUARD: Get in the line!
Get moving!

13:25.014 --> 13:27.391
PRISONER: Boy,
take a look at those!

13:29.101 --> 13:30.936
Move your fuckin' arse.

13:33.355 --> 13:34.523
Who's that?

13:49.413 --> 13:50.664
(SCOFFS)

14:01.008 --> 14:02.926
MAN: Hey, Goldberg!

14:03.093 --> 14:04.219
PRISONER:
Yeah, that's right.

14:04.345 --> 14:07.848
I'm a big fan. But we've got
our own bitches down here.

14:08.807 --> 14:10.408
I don't know why you
brought yours along.

14:11.685 --> 14:13.006
Hey, let me give
you an autograph.

14:13.062 --> 14:14.438
Move! Move!

14:14.521 --> 14:15.898
(ALL SCREAM)

14:15.981 --> 14:17.232
(CLAMORING)

14:20.861 --> 14:22.279
(KATRINA SCREAMS)

14:25.032 --> 14:26.784
Let's take this fucking joint!

14:27.034 --> 14:28.410
(ALL GRUNTING)

14:57.773 --> 14:59.274
Kill them all!

14:59.400 --> 15:02.528
GUARD 1: Set up a perimeter now.
GUARD 2: On the ground, now!

15:05.823 --> 15:06.990
(BOTH GRUNTING)

15:20.838 --> 15:21.839
Shit!

15:37.521 --> 15:38.814
Get up! (GROANS)

15:54.037 --> 15:55.622
(BONES CRACKING)

16:10.971 --> 16:14.099
Are you hurt? What?

16:16.059 --> 16:17.311
(GASPS)

16:20.898 --> 16:24.318
Lucas.
It always was you.

16:26.278 --> 16:28.155
You son of a bitch!

16:30.991 --> 16:32.701
We thought you were dead.

16:33.285 --> 16:35.162
So it's always been
you behind the mask.

16:36.038 --> 16:37.998
Yeah, it's a long story.

16:38.081 --> 16:39.750
So what kind of deal
did they make, huh?

16:40.459 --> 16:41.668
I didn't have a choice.

16:41.752 --> 16:42.836
(SIGHS IN EXASPERATION)

16:42.920 --> 16:45.589
Whatever it was, it included
getting your face fixed.

16:45.672 --> 16:47.132
I saw it.
I was there.

16:47.299 --> 16:48.425
Did you, Goldberg?

16:48.842 --> 16:50.722
Or did you just see what
they wanted you to see?

16:50.761 --> 16:52.095
What did they want us to see?

16:53.013 --> 16:54.515
That is no deal.

16:54.598 --> 16:55.933
You never needed
to make a deal.

16:56.016 --> 16:58.810
All you had to do was win five
races in a row and you're free.

16:58.894 --> 17:00.229
Those are the rules.

17:01.688 --> 17:04.148
There are no rules
in the cage, Lists.

17:04.775 --> 17:06.818
At least none that
benefit the cage.

17:07.569 --> 17:09.195
Believe what you want,
Goldberg.

17:09.404 --> 17:12.449
But I don't think it's wise, right
now, that they see us together.

17:19.957 --> 17:21.458
Welcome to hell.

17:25.212 --> 17:26.713
(MUMBLING)

17:28.423 --> 17:31.051
Keep moving, don't stop!
Come on!

17:31.510 --> 17:33.804
Come on, come on,
come on, come on.

17:34.012 --> 17:37.808
Welcome to Kalahari Prison.
You dare try and escape,

17:38.058 --> 17:41.895
the desert will kill you before we do.
Come on, move!

17:46.483 --> 17:48.235
(PRISONERS JEERING)

18:00.330 --> 18:02.708
(SHOUTING IN
FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

18:15.345 --> 18:16.722
You all right?

18:42.164 --> 18:43.290
GUARD: Close the gate.

19:24.956 --> 19:26.416
Hey, Goldberg.

19:28.418 --> 19:31.213
She's bigger and better.

19:31.296 --> 19:34.007
Way bigger.
Way better.

19:45.644 --> 19:47.938
I've been through
more shit in my life

19:48.438 --> 19:50.440
than most people
go through in 10.

19:51.942 --> 19:55.862
But what I never did was
lie or betray my friends.

19:56.863 --> 19:58.464
Doesn't matter what
your intentions were,

19:59.282 --> 20:01.159
your secret would have
been safe with us.

20:02.494 --> 20:03.495
We could've helped.

20:03.578 --> 20:05.122
You know better than that.

20:05.205 --> 20:08.291
Helping me comes with a price, and
I wasn't about to let you do that.

20:11.461 --> 20:12.629
You believe in curses?

20:13.630 --> 20:14.798
This thing.

20:16.216 --> 20:17.217
It comes with one.

20:18.301 --> 20:19.469
You should've trusted us.

20:25.892 --> 20:27.269
Let's go, Lists.

20:53.837 --> 20:56.840
ANNOUNCER: <i> Live from Kalahari
Prison in South Africa,</i>

20:57.007 --> 21:00.135
<i>this is</i> Death Race
Navigator Wars.

21:01.011 --> 21:03.096
<i>Featuring 16
of the most beautiful,</i>

21:03.180 --> 21:05.932
<i>ruthless and lethal
convicts alive,</i>

21:06.016 --> 21:09.603
<i>including an IRA terrorist,
a contract killer,</i>

21:09.686 --> 21:12.105
<i>even identical twin
serial killers.</i>

21:12.272 --> 21:15.358
<i>But all eyes will be
on Katrina Banks,</i>

21:15.525 --> 21:19.029
<i>the gorgeous copilot of
the notorious Frankenstein.</i>

21:20.614 --> 21:25.368
<i>This is a match to the death.
The only rule, survive.</i>

21:29.539 --> 21:30.916
What the hell is happening?

21:32.209 --> 21:36.671
Good evening and welcome to a
special <i>pre-Death Race</i> event.

21:36.755 --> 21:39.341
Sixteen beautiful,
yet deadly women,

21:39.674 --> 21:43.136
vie for 10 spots
as <i>Death Race</i> navigators.

21:45.180 --> 21:49.351
These ladies will battle to
the death to see who's worthy

21:49.559 --> 21:52.896
to navigate in
tomorrow's <i>Death Race.</i>

21:55.065 --> 21:56.483
ANNOUNCER: <i> After the
first three minutes,</i>

21:56.566 --> 21:59.027
<i>pressure plates activate
a variety of lethal weapons.</i>

21:59.110 --> 22:01.696
<i>The fight ends when
10 ladies are left alive.</i>

22:01.780 --> 22:04.616
Katrina's statistical probability
of survival is very low.

22:04.699 --> 22:06.743
And the Swedish twins aren't
gonna fight each other.

22:06.827 --> 22:09.079
Plus, Katrina's celebrity
will attract more attention.

22:09.287 --> 22:10.664
That changes the odds.

22:10.747 --> 22:12.082
So, what are you saying?

22:12.415 --> 22:13.583
Seven to 10%.

22:14.709 --> 22:15.794
Best case scenario.

22:16.586 --> 22:20.006
ANNOUNCER: <i> Dim the lights.
The carnage is about to begin.</i>

22:20.257 --> 22:21.925
(WOMEN GROANING)

22:29.808 --> 22:31.101
Katrina, kick some ass!

22:47.284 --> 22:50.453
Do I know my audience or what?

22:52.706 --> 22:54.374
(WOMEN SCREAMING)

22:56.710 --> 23:00.297
That's reality TV shit.
Come on.

23:03.466 --> 23:04.509
Yes.

23:05.302 --> 23:07.637
ANNOUNCER: <i> Pressure
plates are now active.</i>

23:09.055 --> 23:10.432
